We will get blink app from play store on phone.
In the first, we open the app. Then we select the plus bottton. After that we write project name and select ESP8266. Then create.
-- Application will send token to email that we sign in. We will use this token in arduino. --
We select the botton that in project again. And select button. Then we will push button. We will go to button setting. We go to output section.
Select pin, We choose digital and gp16. Then OK. It finishes.
When we want to run program. We will use the button pause to run program but we need to connect wi-fi in the first.
